{
  "texts": [
    "Of these genes, 24.1% (2,169/8,995) had a plasmid-associated keyword in their COG/Pfam annotations (see the 'Keyword analysis of COGs and Pfams for plasmid functions' section).",
    "We also used the 24,168 genes that were always classified as cargo genes and never backbone genes in any plasmid system.",
    "Among these genes, 13.4% (3,229/24,168) had a plasmid-associated keyword.",
    "We excluded the 1,917 genes that were sometimes classified as backbone genes and other times cargo genes, depending on the system, from the analysis.",
    "We also excluded 12,092 genes that were on compound plasmids but were classified as backbone genes, as these genes are redundant with the backbone genes that were encoded on the backbone plasmid."
  ]
}